1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 7 MRSA §604, sub-§22-A, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 673, §1, is amended
3 to read:
4 22-A. Perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances or PFAS. "Perfluoroalkyl
5 and polyfluoroalkyl substances" or "PFAS" has the same meaning as in Title 32, section
6 1732, subsection 5‑A 40 Code of Federal Regulations, Section 705.3, as amended.
7 Sec. 2. 38 MRSA §1614, sub-§5, ¶H is enacted to read:
8 H. Notwithstanding subsection 1, paragraph F, for purposes of the prohibition on the
9 sale of pesticide products containing intentionally added PFAS under this subsection,
10 "perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances" or "PFAS" has the same meaning as
11 in Title 7, section 604, subsection 22-A and "pesticide" has the same meaning as in
12 Title 7, section 604, subsection 25.
13 SUMMARY
1144 This bill changes the definition of "perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances,"
1155 also referred to as PFAS, in the Maine Pesticide Control Act of 1975 to align with the
1166 United States Environmental Protection Agency's definition of "PFAS." The bill also
1177 applies this definition of PFAS for the purposes of the prohibition on the sale of pesticide
1188 products containing intentionally added PFAS.
